# Configuration

{{ project_name }} uses TOML-based configuration with Pydantic for validation.

## Configuration Files

Configuration is loaded from multiple locations in priority order:

1. `/etc/{{ project_slug }}/config.toml` - System-wide (lowest priority)
2. `~/.{{ project_slug }}/config.toml` - User-specific
3. `{{ project_slug }}.toml` - Project-specific (highest priority)

Later configurations override earlier ones.

## Configuration Schema
```toml
# Project settings
project_name = "{{ project_name }}"
debug = false

# Workspace paths
[workspace]
data_dir = "data"
output_dir = "outputs"
models_dir = "models"
cache_dir = ".cache"
```

## Using Configuration
```python
from {{ module_name }} import CONF

# Access workspace paths
print(CONF.workspace.data_dir)
print(CONF.workspace.output_dir)

# Create workspace directories
CONF.workspace.ensure_directories()

# Access settings
print(CONF.project_name)
print(CONF.debug)
```

## Creating Custom Configuration

Create a file `{{ project_slug }}.toml` in your project root:
```toml
project_name = "My Custom Project"
debug = true

[workspace]
data_dir = "/path/to/data"
output_dir = "/path/to/outputs"
```

The configuration will be automatically loaded when you import the module.